<body>
Reports alias expressions that duplicate names of columns in tables and might be redundant.
<p>Example (PostgreSQL):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE foo(a INT, b INT);

SELECT * FROM foo foo(a, b);
SELECT * FROM foo foo(a);
SELECT * FROM foo foo(x);
SELECT * FROM foo foo(x, y);</code></pre>
<p>The first two aliases use the same column names as in the <code>foo</code> table. They are considered redundant because they
  column names are identical.</p>
